divs: Sighting DetailsIt was a beautiful sunny weather, no single cloud in the sky. I was sitting in my room and looked at the sky, a few seconds later I saw a white(ish) circle-shaped object moving quite fast. Can't really say how fast and how far away it was... It took it approx. 10-12 seconds to disappear behind a building. Unfortunately I was too slow to take a picture. BUT! A few minutes later I saw a similar object moving in the same direction. This time I took my camera and took 2 pics. It is very small. At first I thought it was a helicopter but I think it was too fast and it doesn't really look like one. Definitely doesn't look like a plane, does it? I think it might be a bird but I'm sending two pics to you just in case. Sorry the pics are so big but thanks to that you can see that object more clearly.
